<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-16T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-16T16:00:00-05:00" n="923" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d923">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 855.48/508a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJE1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Willard</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-16T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>328. For Berlin. Norwegian steamer <hi rend="italic">Storstad</hi> under
                            charter to Commission for Relief in Belgium carrying 10,000 tons corn
                            from <pb facs="0825" n="653" xml:id="pg_653"/> Buenos Aires to
                            Rotterdam, was sunk without warning by German submarine off coast of
                            Ireland, March 7 or 8. German Government will, of course, recognize that
                            sinking of commission’s ships in violation of understanding strikes at
                            the root of relief work in Belgium and northern France. This Government
                            can not encourage commission to continue its work unless it has most
                            positive assurances that no more of its ships will be sunk.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>